This is where I learned how to eat noodle with this fried soybean sauce: mix it well with all the ingredients! If you don't want it too salty, don't mix it all! Very interesting indeed. We ordered local beer and a peach juice (the waiter brought a box of one liter!)

My classic and favourite lunch place when in Beijing. Yes, it's noisy and crowded but the food is great and you don't feel very much like a tourist. Don't miss the local Fried bean sauce of course but try also any of the other dishes, all are perfectly prepared.
great taste and well presented, our guide ordered lunch and the selection was most tasty, you add what you want with the noodles, very enjoyable.
